          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-03-09T18:16:56Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Second Chance for Students Act</b></p> <p>This bill modifies federal student aid eligibility for a student who is convicted of a drug offense involving marijuana possession.</p> <p>Under current law, a drug offense conviction involving the sale or possession of a controlled substance triggers a suspension of federal student aid eligibility for a specified period of time. This bill allows a student who is convicted of a drug offense involving marijuana possession, without the intent to distribute, to resume or retain federal student aid eligibility while completing a drug rehabilitation program.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-07-26T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
